20/05/2011
MADRID, Spain -- Six people have been arrested in Spain in an anti-drug operation conducted by local police and Serbia's Security and Information Agency (BIA), the BIA announced on Thursday (May 19th). The three Serbs and three Montenegrins are suspected of smuggling drugs from South America. Police have seized 77kg of cocaine during the course of their operation. The drugs, planted aboard a ship from Argentina, were discovered in the port of Tarragona. (RTS, Tanjug, Radio Free Europe, B92 - 19/05/11)
